OL,3,C'Bankrupt' Birmingham confirms #148m
OL,4,Cof council cuts in second budget blow
OL,6,FCentral government funding allocations
OL,7,Fhave steadily declined, leaving many
OL,8,Fcouncils across the UK teetering on
OL,9,Fthe brink, ITV News Deputy Political
OL,10,FEditor Anushka Asthana explains
OL,12,FThere is more pain to come for those
OL,13,Fwho rely on council services in
OL,14,FBirmingham as the struggling local
OL,15,Fauthority today outlined plans to cut
OL,16,F#148 million from its budget this year.
OL,18,FOver half of the savings, #43m, have
OL,19,Fbeen found in cuts to adult social
OL,20,Fcare, and #39m in children and
OL,21,Ffamilies services.
