OL,6,FOpposition parties, particularly the
OL,7,FConservatives and Liberal Democrats,
OL,8,Fare eager to capitalise on Labour's
OL,9,Fperceived mismanagement, framing the
OL,10,Ffinancial crisis as a failure of
OL,11,Fgovernance rather than just an issue
OL,12,Fof central government underfunding.
OL,14,FLabour, which has long controlled the
OL,15,Fcouncil, is facing a political
OL,16,Freckoning. The upcoming 2026 local
OL,17,Felections could see their grip on
OL,18,Fpower seriously threatened, as
OL,19,Fdisillusioned voters look for
OL,20,Falternatives.
