OL,6,FBut the question of blame is far from
OL,7,Fstraightforward. While critics argue
OL,8,Fthat Labour's handling of equal pay
OL,9,Fclaims and budgeting has exacerbated
OL,10,Fthe crisis, the wider context cannot
OL,11,Fbe ignored.
OL,13,FCentral government funding allocations
OL,14,Fhave steadily declined, leaving many
OL,15,Fcouncils across the UK teetering on
OL,16,Fthe brink.
