OL,3,C'Bankrupt' Birmingham confirms #148m
OL,4,Cof council cuts in second budget blow
OL,6,FAs the city heads toward another year
OL,7,Fof painful decisions, one thing is
OL,8,Fcertain: the fight over Birmingham's
OL,9,Ffinancial future is not just about
OL,10,Fbudgets, but about the trust and
OL,11,Fcredibility of those in power.
OL,13,FLabour faces a battle not only to keep
OL,14,Fcontrol of the council but to convince
OL,15,Fvoters that it is capable of pulling
OL,16,Fthe city out of its financial tailspin.
OL,18,FIf it fails, Birmingham could become a
OL,19,Fcautionary tale for local governments
OL,20,Facross the country.
